07/05/2006
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- US Vice President Dick Cheney voiced strong support for the efforts of the US-Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- to join Euro-Atlantic structures, during a meeting with the prime ministers of the three states in Dubrovnik Sunday (7 May).
He praised the progress achieved in the reform process, as well as the countries' participation in the operations in Iraq and Afghanistan.
At the meeting, Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha, Croatia's Ivo Sanader and Macedonia's Vlado Buckovski reiterated expectations that the NATO summit in Riga later this year would provide a clear signal regarding their countries' prospects for membership in the Alliance.
(HRT - 07/05/06;
HINA, Bloomberg, AP, AFP, Reuters, UPI - 06/05/06)
